article.description: — Damen Thacker had 22 points as Idaho ended its season-opening 19-game losing streak, edging past Montana State 74-69 on Friday.
article.headline: Thacker scores 22 to lift Idaho past Montana St. 74-69
article.linkText: Thacker scores 22 to lift Idaho past Montana St. 74-69
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho -- — Damen Thacker had 22 points as Idaho ended its season-opening 19-game losing streak, edging past Montana State 74-69 on Friday. Ja’Vary Christmas had 11 points for Idaho (1-19, 1-16 Big Sky Conference). Idaho scored 38 points in the first half, a season high for the team. Jubrile Belo scored a season-high 24 points for the Bobcats (9-8, 6-5), whose losing streak stretched to five games. Xavier Bishop added 14 points and seven assists. Amin Adamu had 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
